Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Quarter the @cauliflower{1}(quartered) with your hands. Grate on the coarse side of your #grater{} to make 'rice'.

Halve, peel and quarter the @onion{1}(peeled and quartered), then separate the layers.

Pop the onion onto a lined #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{to taste} and @balsamic vinegar{1%sachet}, then season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until softened, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> TIP: You can use a food processor to make the rice if you've got one.

== Parsley Butter ==

Peel and grate the @garlic{1}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Finely chop the @parsley{5%g}(finely chopped) (stalks and all).

Put @butter{2%tbsp} (double for 4) in a #small bowl{} and mash with a #fork{} until soft. Stir in the garlic and parsley. Set aside.

== Steak ==

Season the @Irish beef rump{250%g}(seasoned) with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Place a #large pan{} over high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, lay the beef into the pan. Fry until browned, ~{2-3%minutes} on each side.

Lower heat to medium and cook for another ~{1-2%minutes} on each side if you want it medium-rare.

Once done, remove from pan. Cover and allow to rest. Meat is safe to eat when outside is browned.

> TIP: Cook for 1-2 mins extra on each side if you like it more well done.

== Broccoli ==

Return the (now empty) pan to medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, add the @broccoli{1}(cut into florets) to the pan and fry for ~{2-3%minutes}, then add a splash of @water{to taste}.

Pop a #lid{} on the pan, or cover in #foil{}, and cook until tender, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Set the broccoli aside and wipe the pan.

== Cauliflower Rice ==

Return the pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste} and a knob of @butter{to taste}.

When hot, add the cauliflower rice and cook until slightly softened, ~{3-4%minutes}, stirring regularly.

Remove from the heat. Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

== To Serve ==

Divide the cauliflower rice, broccoli and roasted onion between plates.

Slice the steak and serve alongside.

Finish with a spoon of garlic parsley butter.